## Description

Download the dataset by clicking on the 'ZIP' button at the top right of this page.  The zip file contains an Excel spreadsheet listing appropriate plants recommended for sidewalks, private backyards and roofs that are adapted to San Francisco's unique environment, climate and habitats. These plants were selected with urban sustainability, biodiversity, and water conservation practices in mind due to their drought tolerance and provision of habitat for wildlife.  The zip file also contains a GIS shapefile of plant community areas (areas appropriate for specific communities of plants, aka "phytocoenosis" or "phytocenosis"). The plant database and plant community shapefile are used in the San Francisco Plant Finder website (http://sfplantfinder.org) which allows to you search for an address or click on a map and view details of plants recommended for that location.
